    <div class="container">
	
	<p>Greetings, I am David Lobser.  I have an extensive background in 3D animation and I am embarking on a quest to apply my skills to the interactive world.  I spent some time trying to decide where to go after
	processing.  It was either in the direction of lower level C based coding with Open Frameworks and Cinder, Unity, or some framework in Javascript.  I was planning to stay away from 3D as much as possible but threejs 
	sucked me in.  It's a pretty full featured 3D package without the front end, so I can comfortably use tools I'm familiar with while picking up some brand new skills along the way.  I'm enjoying the flexibility of 
	Javascript and the power of webGL, but html/css are huge headaches for me.  I'm going to attempt to document my process and try to keep relatively clean code while attempting to build the skills I need to do a 
	few key projects:</p>
	<li>A modeling tool that can export to shapeways automatically</li>
	<li>A darwin pond of spawning creatures</li>
	<li>A short interactive narrative piece</li>
	<li>A collection of resources I can reference later, and hopefully others as well<li>

